author: Paul McTaggart
title: Flood warnings still in place across Cumbria | News and Star
text: Three flood warnings are still in place in Cumbria following the heavy rain and stormy conditions. The warnings remain in place at Keswick Campsite, Rickerby Park, the River Eden at [Carlisle](/sport/football/carlisle-united/), and Swifts and Stoneyholm Golf Courses, according to the latest update. Seven flood alerts are also still in place across Cumbria, in which flooding is still possible with more rainfall expected to hit the region today (December 29). - Lower River Eden - Rivers Brathay, Rothay and Winster - Rivers Duddon, Crake and Mill Beck - Rivers Lowther and Eamont - Upper River Aire catchment - Upper River Derwent, Stonethwaite Beck and Derwent Water - Upper River Lune 17 flood warnings have been removed in the last 24 hours. ⚠️ 7 flood alerts are still in place today! Flooding is possible.— Cumbria Flood Update (@CumbriaFloods) ⚠️ 3 flood warnings are in place today! Flooding is expected. ❌ 17 flood warnings removed [#CumbriaFloods] [#Cumbria] [pic.twitter.com/XA12XBoliZ] [December 28, 2023] - Lower River Lune and Conder - Middle River Eden - River North Tyne - River Rede - Rivers Caldew and Petteril - Rivers Ehen, Calder, Irt and Esk - Rivers Esk and Irthing - Rivers Greta, St Johns Beck and Bassenthwaite Lake - Rivers Kent and Bela - Rivers Wampool and Ellen - Upper River Eden - Upper River Ribble, Hodder - Upper River Swale - Upper River Tees - Upper River Ure - Upper River Wear - Upper River Wharfe Comments: Our rules We want our comments to be a lively and valuable part of our community - a place where readers can debate and engage with the most important local issues.
